sac.stats

Class Stats

  • java.lang.Object
    • sac.stats.Stats

  • public class Stats
extends java.lang.Object
    Statistics object, meant to memorize quantities of interest from a search algorithm after its execution has been finished.
    Author:
    Przemysław Klęsk (wi.zut.edu.pl), Marcin Korzeń (wi.zut.edu.pl)

    • Method Detail

      • addEntry

        public void addEntry(java.lang.String category,
            double value,
            java.lang.Object... multiIndex)
        Adds an entry into this statistics object for given category, value and multi index.
        Parameters:
        category - category (quantity of interest) as string
        value - value to be memorized for given category
        multiIndex - multi index for the entry (typically, multi index is defined by a vector of current loop indices in an experiment)

      • addEntries

        public void addEntries(SearchAlgorithm algorithm,
              java.lang.Object... multiIndex)
        Adds entries into this statistics object for multiple categories of search algorithm and given multi index. This method checks inside if given algorithm is an instance of GraphSearchAlgorithm or GameSearchAlgorithm.
        Parameters:
        algorithm - reference to search algorithm
        multiIndex - multi index for entries (typically, multi index is defined by a vector of current loop indices in an experiment)

      • values

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Double> values(java.lang.String category,
                                      java.lang.Object... multiIndexPattern)
        Returns a list of all values memorized for given category and multi index pattern (the pattern may contain nulls working as 'any').
        Parameters:
        category - category (quantity of interest) as string
        multiIndexPattern - multi index pattern (may contain nulls)
        Returns:
        list of values memorized for given category and multi index pattern
